# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Nightjar .gitignore — local-first AI assistant (AGPL-3.0-or-later)
# Goal: keep source + docs + config + license/attribution; exclude secrets,
# machine/user data, huge model weights, and re-generatable/vendored trees.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Secrets / credentials / accounts (defensive — NONE are committed today) ──
# Real email/CalDAV creds are Fernet-encrypted into ~/.nightjar/odysseus (OUTSIDE
# this repo); these patterns make sure a stray copy never lands in git.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.env
.envrc
accounts.json
secrets.json
credentials.json
*.credentials
*secret*.json
# Odysseus key material (normally ~/.nightjar/odysseus/.app_key & .key)
.app_key
.key
# Keys / certs
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
*.der
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
*_rsa
*.keystore

# ── Nightjar runtime data dir (in case DATA_DIR is ever pointed into the repo) ─
.nightjar/
**/.nightjar/

# ── Model weights / large binaries (live in ~/.nightjar/models & ~/models) ────
*.gguf
*.ggml
*.onnx
*.safetensors
*.pt
*.pth
*.bin
voices-*.bin
Modelfile.*
# Ollama blobs (normally ~/.ollama — ignore defensively if ever copied in)
.ollama/

# ── Python ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/
**/venv/
**/.venv/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── Node / JS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
**/node_modules/
.npm/
.pnpm-store/
# (package-lock.json / pnpm-lock.yaml are KEPT — reproducible installs)

# ── Build / bundler output (re-generatable) ──────────────────────────────────
dist/
build/
out/
**/out/
.vite/
**/.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ── Logs / temp ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/
tts_out.wav
*.tmp
.cache/

# ── Vendored / cloned UPSTREAM reference repos (each is its own huge git repo) ─
# research/ holds full clones of Row-Bot, Open WebUI, orb-ui, gemma-chat (~3 GB,
# each with its own .git) — re-clonable development references, ignored.
# EXCEPTIONS (git SUBMODULES, see .gitmodules): research/opencode (the OpenCode
# agent engine — the ONLY agent loop, a runtime dependency; pinned to
# sst/opencode@7a8e7c8 via the AxeH666/opencode fork for durability) and
# research/odysseus (a runtime dependency AND the AGPL source-availability
# obligation). Both are tracked as gitlinks and fetched via `git submodule
# update --init`. Nightjar's changes to odysseus live as a patch in
# phase2-odysseus/odysseus-patches/ (that submodule stays a clean upstream
# mirror). Row-Bot's shipped code is vendored under
# phase2-mcp/nightjar_capabilities/_vendor/ (+ NOTICE + LICENSE.row-bot).
research/*
!research/odysseus
!research/opencode
# Nightjar-authored planning docs that happen to live in research/ (the README
# links to them as the master plan) — these ARE part of the repo; only the
# upstream CLONE directories above are ignored.
!research/AUDIT_REPORT.md
!research/ODYSSEUS_INTEGRATION_PLAN.md
!research/PROVIDER_SELECTION_PLAN.md
!research/5b_PLAN.md

# ── OS / editor cruft ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
# VS Code: keep shared settings if you add them; ignore per-machine noise
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/settings.json

# ── Local tooling state ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.openforge/

# ── Live-preview build output (AUDIT §10 #4) ─────────────────────────────────
# The coding agent writes previewable web artifacts here. Keeping it untracked
# means the git-gate safety plugin never sees it in `git status`, so multi-file
# design builds are never rolled back mid-generation (agent re-reads stay valid).
phase2-odysseus/workspace/preview/

# ── CAD export artifacts (test / agent output) ───────────────────────────────
# STEP/STL/GLB the CAD agent or tests emit into the workspace are generated, not
# source (e.g. a stray demo_car.step). Ignore them so they don't clutter status.
phase2-odysseus/workspace/*.step
phase2-odysseus/workspace/*.stl
phase2-odysseus/workspace/*.glb
